            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.36.18-21_0001" />
                <note type="curatorial">161-3                           Aly Collection</note>                       <fw type="curatorial">18</fw>
                
                <opener>
                <dateline>5-19-62</dateline>
                
                
                
                <salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>This is for the record. Also, I feel you'll want to know about the Library Dinner last evening (May 18). It was a glorious affair. When the bust was presented (with a lovely speech) and the <hi rend="underline">citation of merit</hi> read, the response was explosive &#8212; a "standing ovation" <hi rend="underline">and a feeling of affection that</hi> filled the <hi rend="underline">place</hi>. It was one of the best things that a crowd ever did to me. The Nebraska affair was, of course, grander, more impressive; but this was intimate, loving, precious. I wish you had been there.</p> 
               
                <p>On the 26th I'll do the honors at the Willa Cather banquet and dedicate the memorial to her.</p>
                
                <p><hi rend="underline">I am making strong medicine for Bower</hi>!!</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>Love always &#8212;</salute> <signed>John.</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
